## D012: Technology Stack — Astro + MDX + Svelte Islands + D3/Layercake
**Date**: 2026-03-02
**Status**: DECIDED

**Observation**: Four candidates evaluated through full differential diagnosis with consensus-or-parsimony discriminator through Orders 0–4:

| Candidate | Order 0 | Order 1 | Order 2 | Order 3 | Trajectory |
|-----------|---------|---------|---------|---------|------------|
| TS2 Astro+Svelte | 20/25 | 23/25 | 19.6/25 | 18.3/25 | STABLE |
| TS1 Next.js+React | 19/25 | 17/25 | — | — | DECLINING |
| TS3 SvelteKit | 17/25 | — | — | — | ELIMINATED |
| TS4 11ty | 15/25 | — | — | — | ELIMINATED |

**Decision**: Astro + MDX + Svelte Islands + D3/Layercake for visualizations. Single Astro project with CDN-level domain routing for dual-domain architecture.

**Reasoning**:
- **Parsimony wins**: Astro treats content as primary artifact and interactivity as islands within content — matching a content-first advocacy site. Next.js treats interactivity as primary and content as data, creating impedance mismatch.
- **Progressive enhancement for free**: Astro ships zero JS by default; all content renders as static HTML; islands hydrate only interactive components
- **Lens system via CSS + islands**: data-lens attribute on body drives CSS layout transformation (<100ms); Svelte islands receive lens as prop for viz variants
- **Viz ecosystem unlocked**: Astro's framework-agnostic islands avoid the React-D3 DOM control tension; D3 and Layercake both work natively
- **Accessibility strongest**: HTML-first output provides the best baseline for WCAG 2.1 AA; semantic structure exists without JS hydration
- **Ecosystem hedged**: HTML output survives framework death; content in MDX files remains portable

**What follows**:
- Initialize Astro project with MDX and Svelte integrations
- Implement lens system as CSS-driven layout + Svelte island LensProvider
- Content collections for analysis documents (typed frontmatter)
- Single codebase, single build, domain routing at CDN level
- `/discriminate` skill created to encode the methodology used for this and all prior decisions

