## D018: Light Mode Default + Dark Theme Toggle
**Date**: 2026-03-02
**Status**: DECIDED

**Observation**: The dark terminal palette (#002d38 background) from kashifshah.net
works well for the developer/researcher audience but limits accessibility and feels
unfamiliar to the primary voter and educator audiences. The marketing strategy targets
voters first, educators second — both audiences expect light backgrounds. Printing
from dark mode consumes excessive ink.

**Alternatives considered**:
- A: Keep dark-only, rely on PrintLayout for light needs — limits reach
- B: Add light mode, keep dark as default — conservative, unclear user benefit
- C: Add light mode, make light the default, dark available via toggle — centers
  the advocacy audience while preserving the terminal aesthetic for developers

**Decision**: Option C. Restructure CSS variables so `:root` contains light palette
values (new default). Current dark terminal palette moved to `[data-theme="dark"]`
selector. ThemeToggle.svelte component provides switching. Blocking `<script>` in
`<head>` prevents flash-of-wrong-theme.

**Reasoning**:
- Light backgrounds read as more trustworthy to general/non-technical audiences
- Voters and educators (primary personas) operate in light-mode environments
- `prefers-color-scheme: dark` OS setting automatically triggers dark mode
- Blocking script eliminates flash by setting `data-theme` before first paint
- CSS custom properties make the switch zero-cost — all selectors use `var()`
- RatificationMap and CausalChain hardcoded colors converted to CSS variables
  with SSR-safe fallbacks (light defaults during build, resolved at runtime)

**What follows**:
- Map and chain colors now theme-aware via MutationObserver on `data-theme`
- `meta[name="theme-color"]` updates dynamically per selected theme
- Theme preference persists in localStorage (`unratified-theme`)
- PrintLayout remains independent (loads zero base.css)
- Light palette: #fafafa bg, #37474f text, #33691e headings, #00695c links
- Dark palette: #002d38 bg, #98a8a8 text, #819500 headings, #259d94 links

